ot responding.";i:11;s:40:"This could indicate a bad circuit board.";i:12;s:94:"Thunderstorms with their dramatic lightning strikes can be as damaging as they are impressive.";i:13;s:109:"If your LiftMaster garage door is stuck and wont open it is possible to troubleshoot it in a variety of ways.";i:14;s:110:"Doors can get stuck due to problems with their power source photo eyes and track alignment among other things.";i:15;s:118:"Fortunately resolving many of these problems can be done safely by the layperson and doesnt require specialized tools.";i:16;s:142:"Most of the time if youre facing problems opening or closing your garage door though it has power chances are the fault lies with the sensors.";i:17;s:89:"Also try unplugging the garage door opener and re-plugging the unit back into the outlet.";i:18;s:18:"Identify the wire.";i:19;s:45:"Shut off the power to the garage door opener.";i:20;s:38:"Use a screwdriver to tighten the wire.";i:21;s:67:"Turn the power back on and the door should open and close normally.";i:22;s:71:"Some of the most common reasons why your garage door wont open include.";i:23;s:30:"Photo Eye Is Out of Alignment.";i:24;s:54:"The photo eye is the safety sensor on the garage door.";i:25;s:63:"Its job is to detect a person or object in the way of the door.";i:26;s:66:"Reconnect your machine to power and reprogram all remote controls.";i:27;s:46:"Test your garage door with the remote control.";i:28;s:115:"If your garage door wont open when youre attempting to use the keypad its often as simple as replacing the battery.";i:29;s:115:"If that doesnt work follow the reprogramming instructions located on the door to your keypad or in the user manual.";i:30;s:81:"These steps are usually quick simple and usually get to the bottom of your basic.";i:31;s:80:"Yesterday drove up to the garage pressed to open dongle lit up nothing happened.";i:32;s:30:"Other dongle also inoperative.";i:33;s:106:"So Im guessing somethings gone wrong with the power supply 